      "id": "000000000000000000000181",
      "title": "Refactor this function",
      "slug": "prompt-refactor-function",
      "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"html\",{\"html\":\"<pre><code>You are a senior engineer. Refactor the function I paste below for readability, without changing its behaviour. Then list the 3 most important changes as bullets.</code></pre><p>Paste your function right after the prompt. You get the refactor plus a short rationale — perfect for a PR description.</p>\"}]],\"markups\":[],\"sections\":[[10,0],[1,\"p\",[]]]}",
      "feature_image": null,
      "featured": 0,
      "type": "post",
      "status": "published",
      "custom_excerpt": "A reliable refactor prompt that keeps behaviour and explains the changes.",
      "created_at": "2026-07-02T12:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-07-02T12:00:00.000Z",
      "published_at": "2026-07-02T12:00:00.000Z"
     },
     {
      "id": "000000000000000000000182",
      "title": "Explain it like I ship tomorrow",
      "slug": "prompt-explain-practical",
      "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"html\",{\"html\":\"<pre><code>Explain [TOPIC] to a working developer who ships tomorrow. Skip history and theory. Give me: the one-line mental model, the 3 things that bite people, and a minimal example.</code></pre><p>Great for getting productive with a new tool in five minutes instead of an afternoon.</p>\"}]],\"markups\":[],\"sections\":[[10,0],[1,\"p\",[]]]}",
      "feature_image": null,
      "featured": 0,
      "type": "post",
      "status": "published",
      "custom_excerpt": "Cuts the theory — gives you the practical version fast.",
      "created_at": "2026-06-30T12:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-30T12:00:00.000Z",
      "published_at": "2026-06-30T12:00:00.000Z"
     },
     {
      "id": "000000000000000000000183",
      "title": "Debounce in vanilla JS",
      "slug": "snippet-debounce",
      "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"html\",{\"html\":\"<pre><code>const debounce = (fn, ms = 300) => {\\n  let t;\\n  return (...a) => {\\n    clearTimeout(t);\\n    t = setTimeout(() => fn(...a), ms);\\n  };\\n};</code></pre><p>Trailing-edge debounce. For leading-edge, call <code>fn</code> once before starting the timer.</p>\"}]],\"markups\":[],\"sections\":[[10,0],[1,\"p\",[]]]}",
      "feature_image": null,
      "featured": 0,
      "type": "post",
      "status": "published",
      "custom_excerpt": "The trailing debounce I paste into every project.",
      "created_at": "2026-06-28T12:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-28T12:00:00.000Z",
      "published_at": "2026-06-28T12:00:00.000Z"
     },
     {
      "id": "000000000000000000000184",
      "title": "Full-bleed CSS utility",
      "slug": "snippet-full-bleed",
      "mobiledoc": "{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[[\"html\",{\"html\":\"<pre><code>.full-bleed {\\n  width: 100vw;\\n  margin-inline: calc(50% - 50vw);\\n}</code></pre><p>Drop it on any child of a max-width container to make it span the whole viewport width.</p>\"}]],\"markups\":[],\"sections\":[[10,0],[1,\"p\",[]]]}",
      "feature_image": null,
